  "text": "The results are improved somewhat if one fits the the structure function to a polynomial, to remove the oscillations at large separations. We did this by fitting the logarithm of S 2l with a sixth order polynomial, as shown in the left panel of Figure [CITATION_1] . As seen, the behavior at small scales is well captured by the fit while the wiggles at large scales are greatly reduced.",
